(1, 'DO', '<p>Masalah adalah anugerah.\r</p><p>Masalah adalah peluang.\r</p><p>Masalah membuat kita kreatif.\r</p><p>Masalah membuat kita belajar.\r</p><p>Mencari jalan keluar itu mengasyikkan.\r</p><p>Proses mencari solusi itu menyenangkan.\r</p><p>Menemukan solusi itu membahagiakan.\r</p><p>Kreatif itu panggilan jiwa untuk memberi makna.</p>', 6, '2014-03-09', 'Indonesia', 'Handoko Hendroyono', 'Kepustakaan Populer Gramedia', 'Motivasi,Bisnis', '2017-08-06 19:40:24', '2017-08-06 12:40:24', 'DO.jpeg', 'book', 'Book'),
(2, 'Python Machine Learning', '<p>Many of the most innovative breakthroughs and exciting new technologies can be attributed to applications of machine learning. We are living in an age where data comes in abundance, and thanks to the self-learning algorithms from the field of machine learning, we can turn this data into knowledge. Automated speech recognition on our smart phones, web search engines, e-mail spam filters, the recommendation systems of our favorite movie streaming services – machine learning makes it all possible.\r</p><p>\r</p><p>Thanks to the many powerful open-source libraries that have been developed in recent years, machine learning is now right at our fingertips. Python provides the perfect environment to build machine learning systems productively.\r</p><p>\r</p><p>This book will teach you the fundamentals of machine learning and how to utilize these in real-world applications using Python. Step-by-step, you will expand your skill set with the best practices for transforming raw data into useful information, developing learning algorithms efficiently, and evaluating results.\r</p><p>\r</p><p>You will discover the different problem categories that machine learning can solve and explore how to classify objects, predict continuous outcomes with regression analysis, and find hidden structures in data via clustering. You will build your own machine learning system for sentiment analysis and finally, learn how to embed your model into a web app to share with the world</p>', 7, '2015-10-01', 'English', 'Sebastian Raschka', 'Packt Publishing', 'Computer,Programming', '2017-07-04 09:34:04', '2017-08-06 02:34:04', 'Python Machine Learning.jpeg', 'book', 'Book');

